Des_Moines.KDXA:
KDXA (106.3 FM, "Alt 106.3") is an alternative rock radio station serving the Des Moines, Iowa, area. It is located at 106.3 FM. The station's studios are located in Des Moines along with iHeartMedia's other Des Moines stations (KDRB, KKDM, KXNO, and WHO).


== History ==


=== KANY/KJJY: The First 106.3 ===
The first station to occupy the 106.3 frequency was KANY, which signed on in 1978 with 3,000 watts of power.
